==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fratricelli
<hw>Fra`tri*cel"li</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>fraticelli</ets>, lit., little brothers, dim. fr. <ets>frate</ets>
brother, L. <ets>frater</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The name which St. Francis of Assisi gave to his
followers, early in the 13th century.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A sect
which seceded from the Franciscan Order, chiefly in Italy and Sicily, in
1294, repudiating the pope as an apostate, maintaining the duty of
celibacy and poverty, and discountenancing oaths. Called also
<altname>Fratricellians</altname> and
<altname>Fraticelli</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fratricidal</ent>⟦br⟧
